f=Brand Studio/atlas/custom/brand-guidelines/SKILL.md · in=brand-guidelines atlas's enforcement skill: load business's brand-kit file, audit any asset against it, return **PASS itemized fix list**. visual sibling board's constitution-enforcement discipline (quote rule, cite section, never enforce rules never written), applied logos, color, type, spacing, imagery instead governance articles. · p=Brand erosion happens one asset time: slightly-off green here, stretched logo there, new font someone liked. small; sum brand nobody recognizes. skill makes outbound asset auditable against one written kit, consistency enforced process rather whoever happens notice. · wu=Triggers: "on brand check," "visual identity check," "is brand," "audit asset," automatically pixel's asset-pipeline step runs, spark's coherence gate's visual component. for: *creating* identity (that's `brand-identity`, whose output populates kit), layout craft judgments beyond kit's rules (that's `layout-composition`), brand-to-brand separation (that's `multi-brand-system`). · st:/ Protocol=`Load the brand kit (configured path, per brand) \· -> If none exists: STOP — offer assets/brand-kit-template.md, or route to brand-identity \· to create the system first; nothing to enforce \· -> Identify which kit sections apply to this asset type \· -> Audit element by element, quoting the kit rule per finding` · h3:Phase 1 — Load=Read brand kit `brand_kit_path` atlas's config (one path brand business runs). kit stop offer two routes: fill template directly (business already identity, undocumented), run `brand-identity` create system populate template output. Never audit against remembered inferred brand rules. · h3:Phase 2 — Scope=State which kit sections apply asset social graphic touches logo/color/type/imagery; email header maybe logo/color) which don't. Shown output. · h3:Phase 3 — Audit=Element element, against kit's actual text: · h3:Phase 3 — Audit=**Logo**: correct variant context, minimum size, clear space, misuse rules (stretch/rotate/recolor/busy-background)., **Color**: palette-only (name off-palette value found nearest approved token), correct pairings, contrast rule (text brand colors meet kit's accessibility bar WCAG check brand-identity's reference applies audit time too)., **Typography**: approved families/weights only, scale respected, display weights body sizes., **Spacing/layout**: kit's spacing unit clear-space rules (finer layout judgment defers `layout-composition`)., **Imagery**: within kit's photography/illustration direction; rejects named ("stock aesthetic" kit bans it). · h3:Phase 3 — Audit=finding quotes kit rule violates. asset can't fail rule kit doesn't contain gaps kit flagged kit gaps, asset failures. · h3:Phase 4 — Verdict=**PASS** violations; note any kit gaps encountered., **FIX LIST** itemized: rule (quoted, section cited) what's wrong asset specific fix. Ordered visibility violation, discovery order. "make feel on-brand" item actionable. · h3:Phase Drift Note=Repeat findings across assets (same rule violated times, any producer) spark drift note: either production needs correcting kit rule needs revisiting spark operator decide which. · of=`## Brand Audit: [asset, one line] — [brand] \·  \· **Kit:** [file/version loaded] \· **Sections applied:** [list; excluded + why] \·  \· ### Verdict: PASS / FIX LIST` · pr=**No kit, audit.** Enforcement against unwritten rules taste wearing badge., **Quote rule, cite section.** discipline constitution-enforcement., **Asset failures kit gaps.** asset fails written rules; missing rules kit's problem, flagged separately., **Every fix actionable.** "Off-palette: found #2E8B57, nearest approved token color-brand-primary #0E7A4F" never "wrong green.", **Accessibility brand rule.** Contrast failures violations, suggestions, wherever kit (per template) sets WCAG bar., **Repeat findings escalate.** Three violation process kit problem, spark hears about it. · f=Kit path unset file missing stop Phase offer template brand-identity., Kit exists thin (logo-only, color/type rules) audit what's written, list gaps prominently, recommend completing kit template., Asset format unreadable audit what's describable, state what couldn't checked; never PASS unchecked elements., Multiple brands, ambiguous target ask which brand's kit applies; never guess (that's exactly multi-brand bleed risk). · b:with Other atlas Skills=`brand-identity` creates system; skill enforces it. Creation output populates kit; kit skill's law., `layout-composition` owns composition craft kit doesn't legislate; skill enforces what kit says about spacing/clear-space., `multi-brand-system` owns cross-brand separation; skill audits one asset against one brand's kit., Downstream: pixel's asset-pipeline calls audit step; spark's coherence gate includes visual check. Cross-department: lena owns everything about words' *content tone* skill checks text *set* kit.